Product Name: TOZO A1 Mini Wireless Earbuds Bluetooth 5.3 in Ear Light-Weight Headphones Built-in Microphone, IPX5 Waterproof, Immersive Premium Sound Long Distance Connection Headset with Charging Case, Black
Review: Tozo audio products have carved a niche for themselves. Tozo A1 mini is also one of them. It's mini in every sense, comfortable fit for smaller ears, very light weight, 4 pairs of extra small eartips for every type of ears, type C charging cable, bluetooth 5.3 connectivity, AAC/SBC codec Support, upto 23 hours of playback as advertised (6 hours in one charge), IPX5 waterproof rating. It is really one if the best mini earbuds that I have tried/used since 2017. It sits in the ears so comfortably that you can even sleep with them while lying sideways. The sound quality is very good with more of a cleaner and open sound rather than heavy bass. These are loud enough even at 40-50 % volume. The sound output really shines with devices having better hardware/Dolby audio support. The call quality is decent enough that you can hear the other person clearly and vice versa. It doesn't have ANC but good noise isolation. In a crowded place some noises can be heard on both sides of a call. I tested it and didn't find it to be any trouble while taking a call outside. The earbuds last long, touch controls are good and responsive, build quality is also very solid, magnetic case is also very portable and light. Believe me, you won't find a better mini earbuds with so many features at this price range.

Product Name: boAt Airdopes 121v2 in-Ear True Wireless Earbuds with Upto 14 Hours Playback, 8MM Drivers, Battery Indicators, Lightweight Earbuds & Multifunction Controls (Active Black, with Mic)
Review: I recently purchased a Bluetooth earphone from Amazon, hoping to enjoy a seamless audio experience while on the go. However, my experience with this particular product has been nothing short of disappointing. The earphone consistently disconnects after just a few minutes of use, making it incredibly frustrating and inconvenient.One of the most critical aspects of any Bluetooth device is its ability to maintain a stable connection. Unfortunately, this earphone falls short in this regard. Regardless of the device I connect it to, the earphone disconnects randomly, causing interruptions in my audio playback or phone calls. Not only does this disrupt my enjoyment of music and podcasts, but it also hinders my ability to have clear and uninterrupted conversations.Speaking of phone calls, the call quality with this earphone is abysmal. The sound is often distorted, making it difficult for both parties to understand each other clearly. The audio frequently cuts in and out, resulting in fragmented conversations that are frustrating for everyone involved. This issue undermines the purpose of having a hands-free device for making calls on the go, rendering it practically useless.Furthermore, the build quality of the earphone leaves much to be desired. The earbuds themselves feel flimsy and cheaply made. They lack durability and do not provide a secure fit in the ears, which further compromises the overall user experience. Additionally, the buttons on the earphone are not intuitive, making it cumbersome to control music playback or answer calls without referring to the instruction manual.Considering the significant investment I made in this Bluetooth earphone, I expected a product that would deliver on its promises. Unfortunately, it failed to meet even the most basic expectations. The frequent disconnections, poor call quality, and subpar build quality make it impossible for me to recommend this earphone to anyone.I have contacted customer support to address these issues, but their response has been slow and unhelpful. It is evident that this product is plagued with design flaws and functionality issues, and I regret my purchase wholeheartedly.In conclusion, I strongly advise potential buyers to steer clear of this particular Bluetooth earphone. Its unreliable connectivity, poor call quality, and lackluster build quality make it an inferior choice in a market filled with more reliable alternatives. Save yourself the frustration and invest in a better-quality product that will provide a more satisfying audio experience.UserExtremely Dissatisfied with Bluetooth Earphone - Frequent Disconnections and Poor Call QualityChatGPTTitle: An Unfortunate Experience: Bluetooth Earphone Fails to Deliver Reliable PerformanceReview:I recently purchased a Bluetooth earphone from Amazon with high hopes of enjoying wireless convenience and superior audio quality. Regrettably, my experience with this particular product has been nothing short of disappointing. The earphone consistently disconnects after only a few minutes of use, leaving me frustrated and dissatisfied.One of the most crucial aspects of any Bluetooth device is its ability to maintain a stable connection. Sadly, this earphone falls woefully short in that regard. Irrespective of the device I pair it with, the earphone disconnects at random intervals, resulting in frequent interruptions to my audio playback and phone calls. Such inconsistencies not only disrupt my enjoyment of music or podcasts but also hinder my ability to engage in clear and uninterrupted conversations.Moreover, the call quality provided by this earphone is exceptionally poor. Call participants often struggle to understand each other due to distorted sound and frequent audio dropouts. These disruptions render even the simplest conversations unnecessarily frustrating and challenging. The unreliable call quality severely undermines the purpose of using a hands-free device, making it essentially useless for its intended function.Furthermore, the build quality of the earphone leaves much to be desired. The earbuds feel flimsy and poorly constructed, lacking the durability one would expect from a product of this nature. Additionally, they fail to provide a secure and comfortable fit, further compromising the overall user experience. The buttons on the earphone are not intuitively placed, making it cumbersome to control music playback or answer calls without constantly referring to the instruction manual.Given the significant investment I made in this Bluetooth earphone, I had expected a product that would deliver on its promises. Unfortunately, it not only failed to meet my basic expectations but also fell short of industry standards. The frequent disconnections, subpar call quality, and lackluster build quality make it impossible for me to recommend this earphone to others.I have reached out to customer support to address these issues, but their response has been disappointingly slow and unhelpful. It is evident that this product is plagued with design flaws and performance issues, leaving me deeply dissatisfied with my purchase.In conclusion, I strongly advise potential buyers to exercise caution before considering this particular Bluetooth earphone. Its unreliable connectivity, poor call quality, and inferior build quality make it an unsuitable choice when compared to more reliable alternatives available on the market. Spare yourself the frustration and invest in a higher-quality product that will provide a more seamless and enjoyable audio experience.

 Introduction:Over the past 8 days, I have had the pleasure of using an extraordinary Bluetooth earbud that has truly transformed my audio experience. In this comprehensive review, I will delve into the key features that make this earbud a standout performer and explain why I believe it is an absolute game-changer.Bass Performance:One of the standout features of this Bluetooth earbud is its exceptional bass performance. The audio quality is simply remarkable, delivering deep, rich bass that brings music to life. Whether I'm listening to my favorite tracks or immersing myself in a movie, the earbud reproduces the low frequencies with remarkable accuracy and depth. It adds a whole new dimension to my audio experience, allowing me to feel the music and truly appreciate the intricacies of each beat.Fast Charging:The fast charging capability of this earbud is nothing short of impressive. With its advanced charging technology, I can fully charge the earbud in a fraction of the time compared to other wireless earbuds I've used in the past. The convenience of being able to quickly charge the earbud is a game-changer, especially when I'm on the go or in a rush. It ensures that I never have to worry about running out of battery during the day, providing a seamless and uninterrupted audio experience.Ultra-Low Latency:When it comes to wireless audio, latency can often be a concern. However, this Bluetooth earbud has tackled this issue head-on, offering an ultra-low latency experience. Whether I'm watching videos or playing games, the synchronization between audio and visuals is impeccable. The earbud's ability to minimize lag enhances the overall immersion and makes every audio-visual interaction seamless and enjoyable. It truly feels like I'm experiencing the content in real-time, without any noticeable delays.Comfort and Fit:Beyond the remarkable audio performance, this earbud is designed with utmost comfort and a secure fit in mind. The ergonomic design ensures that the earbud stays in place even during rigorous activities or extended periods of use. The earbud's lightweight construction and customizable ear tips contribute to a comfortable fit, allowing me to wear them for extended periods without any discomfort. It's a testament to the thoughtful engineering that goes into creating a truly user-friendly product.Durability and Build Quality:In the time I've spent with this Bluetooth earbud, I have been impressed by its durability and build quality. The earbud feels solid and well-constructed, withstanding the demands of daily use without any signs of wear and tear. The materials used are of high quality, and the earbud's water and sweat resistance make it suitable for various environments, including workouts and outdoor activities. It gives me confidence that this earbud is built to last and withstand the test of time.Conclusion:In conclusion, my 8-day experience with this remarkable Bluetooth earbud has been nothing short of extraordinary. From the impressive bass performance to the fast charging capability and ultra-low latency, this earbud has truly elevated my audio experience. The combination of exceptional audio quality, comfort, durability, and convenience makes it a standout performer in its category. If you're in search of an outstanding Bluetooth earbud that delivers on all fronts, I wholeheartedly recommend giving this one a try. You won't be disappointed!

Product Name: boAt Airdopes 141 Bluetooth Truly Wireless in Ear Headphones with 42H Playtime,Low Latency Mode for Gaming, ENx Tech, IWP, IPX4 Water Resistance, Smooth Touch Controls(Bold Black)
Review: Pros:1. The level of volume it gets to, is just awesome, it can get incredibly loud so if you're at the gym, these are perfect.2. Awesome Bass!3. Noise cancellation is just great, if you simply put them on without even any music playing, u won't be able to hear things around u very well, it's great for places like Gym.4. Lovely battery life, I've had them a week and only had to charge the case once, that too for just a few minutes. And the earbuds themselves, leave them in case for just five min and you'll be getting battery for a long long while.5. They are very comfortable, can be used for long periods of time.6. Affordable!7. The touch controls are very responsive, tap to pause, double tap right one for next song, double tap left one for either rewind or previous song. Can also pick up calls just by tapping.8. Multiple ear coverings are provided with it.9. Type C portCons:1. The sound quality is not bad or anything but it is slightly muffled as compared to good quality headphones etc. The bass is the highlight so it's great for music, but for movies or gaming, you won't get the most crisp audio.2. Some connectivity issues, sometimes i have to turn my Bluetooth on and off many times for it to work (this is occasional, not a daily or frequent occurrence) [Edit after 1 month use: it's now a very frequent issue]3. The mic quality is good if you are using your phone, but for some reason the quality is really bad if you are on PC4. Sometimes on WhatsApp, the mic will not be detected if you are on call with these earbuds, so you will end up having to take them off to accept a call sometimes. (Not an issue if you are the one dialing) i hope it's just a whatsapp issue rather than earbuds issue.Overall, I needed these for my gym since they play horrible music there (lol) so I'm very very happy with themHighly recommended for music and/or as a more affordable option as compared to JBL etc.

 Well, to be honest this is my 2nd Bluetooth earphone. But by far the best in this price range.Included in the bundle accessories are a type C charging cable and extra silicon earplugs. They also shoved in a Rs. 100 cashback voucher offer upon online registration of this product on their website.Coming to the device itself. It's quite cool and comes with tons of features, the first and foremost being 💦 sweat proof. It's absolutely mandatory as people wear these earplugs for long calls.This Maverick earplug has ENC aka Enviornmental Nosie Cancellation, it's not purely Active Noise Cancellation, but quite close to it.Features 4 microphones for uninterrupted audio capture.And the charging case is quite cool, with all those UFO 👽 inspired LEDs. Everytime you open the case or close it, these light start glowing and dimming and repeat. They're dope.As soon as you open the case, the earplugs switch on and start to pair with each other. And when you take them off the case, they automatically pair with the last linked device. Easy peasy.You can use both earplugs or one at a time. I've tried both in the busy streets and honestly this ENC feature is outstanding, almost numbs surrounding noise to the maximum.The user manual is quite self explanatory, the earplugs have tap response, One tap for call receive or cancel on going call. Two taps for redialing last call, or in stereo mode to go to next. Three taps for previous video or song, tried the stereo function on YouTube, works like a charm.I also paired it with my desktop, laptop and Raspberry Pi 4B, works flawlessly with all devices. Pairs easily.This is supposed to be dedicated for gamers, but clearly I'm not, hence can't comment on that, but by definition, it shouldn't lag much.The best thing I liked about it is, the distance it covers. I've tried 8meters till now, while on call, didn't affect a single second. My phone was on ground floor and 1 was on 2nd floor. Honestly, this experiment shouldn't have worked at all, but it did. True Wireless earphones 🎧Coming to the most important part, sound quality. It's marvellous so far. Calls are crystal clear. While listening to music, you can differentiate each beat, the mids are rich and the highs aren't disturbing my ears at all. But yes, it's just been less than 2 days, too early to give anymore details.I've taken a few long calls on this, didn't hurt my ears, those silicon plugs are a boon.Now coming to a few drawbacks I've noticed in last 48hrs.You cannot pair 2 devices at the same time. You have to disconnect from one device and then connect with another one. This is a major drawback in today's scenarios, when we have to work seamlessly across multiple platforms.Another thing I noticed, the tap response isn't very smooth, it lags a bit, before responding to the right tap.I bought it on the 2nd day of its launch, received it the next day with Amazon's super fast delivery. It's not even been 48hrs yet. But over all, this is an absolute steal deal for Rs. 1499. Hopefully I won't discover any more flaws in this device.

Product Name: boAt Airdopes Atom 81 True Wireless Earbuds with Upto 50H Playtime, Quad Mics ENx™ Tech, 13MM Drivers,Super Low Latency(50ms), ASAP™ Charge, BT v5.3(Pearl White)
Review: The sound quality is decent for the 900rs price range. This is not suitable for long calls/meetings. It runs out of battery after 2:45 hrs to 3:00 hrs of talk time. And if you are listening to music or watching a movie/web series, it will last from around 6 hrs to 6:30 hrs. Stand by of this device is really good, it will hardly drain 5% to 10% of the battery for a whole night if you leave it connected to your phone. ASAP charging actually works, we will get another 1.5 hrs of talk time for around 5 min of charging from the charging case. But the percentage of the battery shown right after the ASAP charging is a joke. It shows 80% at first and it drops 10% every minute and stops at 40% after exactly 4 mins.So the takeaway is that1) if you have long meetings and try to cover all of them with this product then you are making a mistake. 2) if you don't have long meetings and want to watch a movie or a web series and want to buy a decent TWS which costs less than 1000rs then this is the best that you can find on the current market.

Product Name: Oppo Enco Buds Bluetooth True Wireless in Ear Earbuds(TWS) with Mic, 24H Battery Life, Supports Dolby Atmos Noise Cancellation During Calls, IP54 Dust & Water Resistant,(Blue, True Wireless)
Review: writing this review after 1.3 year of usage (I had to change the ear-tip in the photo), To be clear I had never used TWS before this, so take my review accordingly...TLDR:Sound - Good,Mic - Bad,Range - 1 Room,Battery - Good,Comfort - Depends on your Ears,Customization - Meh,Detailed Review:Not everyone's ears will welcome these buds, in my case it fitted perfectly in my left ear but not so good in the other. you might suggest to change the ear-tips but no they only provide 3 options (small, med, large). and med one was my only option(which was not fitting in right ear).Earbuds never picked up my voice during calls and the other person on the call always had some issues while speaking with these on, so, If you are the person who has to take a lot of calls then, do NOT take these, I repeat do NOT take these, luckily my daily schedule didn't include lots of call, so I just used these for music and used phone during calls.Now, let's talk about, long usage, again it depends on your ears, I could never wear these more than 3 hours, initially, even when I built habit of wearing these maximum I reached was 5 hrs,please note, I'm not talking about battery-life right now, I'm noting my capacity to wear these on one go..., after such usage my ears would build wax in them, which smelled very bad, so, I had to clean these every week. when I reduced my wearing time to 3 hours again, cleaning requirement stretched to once in 2-3 weeks. Again, this depends on everyone's ears, so you can ignore this paragraph, if this point doesn't apply to you.Coming to battery-life, Good enough for a TWS in this price range,In my case, buds lasted 5-6 hours and the case lasted 3-4 days on full charge which takes 1 hour. please note, I consider myself as mild-user.Talking about range, you better keep your phone with yourself or in your room, cause if you like to run around your house/workplace while keeping your phone at your charging/desk, you will find yourself annoyed with stuttering music.While you can customize the tap gestures with the 'HeyMelody' app, you can only choose from limited options.Talking about features, It has game-mode, which reduces delay in audio, very useful while watching movies/ playing games, which costs more than 1 hours of battery life.Noise Reduction, what is that?...moving on... Dolby Atmos, Just a fancy word for stereo sound.Other Inconvenient moments which I experienced:1. Sometimes (Once/week) your bud will not connect with your phone, so you have to place the bud in the case, close the case, open it again, then wear it again to connect the bud. this will annoy the F out of many.2. You can not fidget-play with case, it is build in a way, you have to use two hands to open it.3. The app we have to use with it, 'HeyMelody', glitches out sometimes, wouldn't show one of the buds.

Product Name: Boult Audio X1 Buds True Wireless in Ear Earbuds with 24H Playtime, Quad Mic ENC, Made in India, Type-C Fast Charging, Environmental Noise Cancellation, 10mm Bass Drivers, TWS Airbass ear buds (Black)
Review: I was looking for reliable Bluetooth earbuds on a budget, and settled on these. Personally, I am pleased with them. I have been using them for almost four months now, including one month when they saw around 12 hours of use per day.PROS:▪ Comfortable.▪ Elegant and sober appearance.▪ Reasonable battery life. I would let the earbuds recharge at, for example, mealtimes.▪ Decent range. Going a few meters into the next room, with a concrete wall in between, was no issue.▪ The battery status of the dock is shown by a series of LED blinks. Simple and practical.CONS:▪ Mediocre phone calling quality. In particular, the microphone. The few conversations I had using these went successfully, so this was not a deal breaker, but the clarity was not the best for sure.The touch controls were initially a drawback for me, but I got used to them. Also, this product does not come with a charger. Either charge off of your computer, or buy a charger with the recommended electrical output. As for the sound quality, it is acceptable, not superlative. I have listened to music, and I have watched films and YouTube videos, with no problem.As a final note, I prefer this type of earbud over the in-ear type, because I find it more hygienic. Wiping with a clean cloth after each use, and leaving the lid of the dock open for some time, should help to slow fungal growth.
